Similar to Goosebumps choose your own horror stories, this was a webGL build used to display and traverse stories with multiple options. 

Multiple stories would be displayed on a main menu screen. Choosing a story would take a user to the first page.

Stories would be written with a specific format in mind and the format would allow the program to parse information and direct the reader appropriately.
Once parsed, the program would update the text and present new choices at the end of the "page".

A scroll rect would allow the user to move through various lines.

Scaling would be necessary to ensure things looked appropriate on various devices. (hardcoded values were selected based on screen size while testing
